modules.description: Provides functions to manipulate structured document elements, including operations for building and traversing blocks, tables, and inline content. Works with nested data types such as lists of blocks, inline elements, and table cells to represent formatted text and tabular data. Used to process and transform document structures in applications like markdown parsers or report generators.

Provides functions to transform and manipulate wikicode blocks and inline elements, including generating and inserting tables of contents, converting links to HTML, normalizing text, and applying open recursive mappings. Operates on block and inline lists from the Wikitext__.Wktxt_type module. Used to process wiki documents by inserting auto-generated tables of contents and converting markup to HTML links.

Handles parsing and rendering of wiki markup, including headers, lists, and links. Operates on strings and abstract syntax trees generated from wiki text. Used to convert user-edited pages into HTML and to process structured data from wiki content.

manipulates structured document elements through block, table, and inline operations, using nested data types to represent and transform formatted content; it supports generating tables of contents, converting links to HTML, and normalizing text, working with block and inline lists to process wiki documents; examples include inserting auto-generated navigation, converting markup to HTML, and restructuring nested content; it enables precise control over document layout and formatting in wiki and markdown processing systems.
